# .env_example
# Copy this file to `.env` and replace the placeholders before running the app.

# Recommended: provide the full MongoDB connection URI (replace <...> values):
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@<cluster-address>/<dbname>?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# Alternatively, you can set components and assemble the URI locally.
# Uncomment and fill these if you prefer to construct the URI yourself.
# MONGO_USER=<username>
# MONGO_PASSWORD=<password>
# MONGO_HOST=<cluster-address>
# MONGO_DB=<dbname>
# Example assembled URI (do not commit secrets):
# MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://$MONGO_USER:$MONGO_PASSWORD@$MONGO_HOST/$MONGO_DB?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# Notes:
# - Do NOT commit your real `.env` file to source control. Add `.env` to .gitignore.
# - The application expects `MONGO_URI` in the environment (see `db_connections.py`).
